Reformulate the object-product transformation using another LEVEL OF DETAIL.
Use a level of description that is too close to the physical phenomenon and too far from the everyday experience solved by a specific technology, so that the Technical System solution is not automatically activated in memory.
The new level of detail must therefore allow the emergence of different technological solutions.
It is noted that a different LEVEL OF DETAIL implies a new OBJECT, new PRODUCT, new TRANSFORMATION and therefore NEW TECHNICAL SYSTEMS (in this case they could be sling/vibration/de-wetting…).
If the new formulation still clearly recalls the initial TECHNICAL SYSTEM, the reformulation is repeated by choosing a different LEVEL OF DETAIL.
Store the information in the 3 vectors OBJECT, PRODUCT, TRANSFORMATION and use them in the following prompts.
(For example for a hairdryer:
OBJECT: hair with droplet; PRODUCT: hair without droplet; TRANSFORMATION: detaching the droplet.
This opens new physical interpretations.)
